  (SELECT COUNT(*)
   FROM comp_cast_type
   WHERE kind = 'crew') AS total_kind,
       t.min_id,
       t.max_id

          MAX(id) AS max_id
   FROM comp_cast_type
   WHERE id BETWEEN '1' AND '3') t;

FROM cast_info AS ci
JOIN movie_info AS mi ON ci.movie_id = mi.movie_id
JOIN title AS t ON mi.movie_id = t.id
JOIN person_info AS pi ON ci.person_id = pi.person_id
JOIN movie_keyword AS mk ON mi.movie_id = mk.movie_id
JOIN movie_companies AS mc ON mi.movie_id = mc.movie_id
JOIN company_name AS cn ON mc.company_id = cn.id
JOIN cast_info AS ci2 ON ci.movie_id = ci2.movie_id
WHERE mi.movie_id = '208'
  AND ci.role_id = '10'
  AND pi.person_id BETWEEN '237' AND '3563';

SELECT m.movie_id,
       COUNT(c.id) AS cast_info_count, -- Aggregation 1
 MIN(t.production_year) AS min_production_year, -- Aggregation 2
 MAX(t.production_year) AS max_production_year, -- Aggregation 3
 AVG(r.id) AS avg_role_id, -- Aggregation 4

  (SELECT SUM(mc2.company_id) -- Aggregation 5 via nested query

   FROM movie_companies mc2
   WHERE mc2.movie_id = m.movie_id) AS nested_sum_company_id
FROM movie_info m
JOIN title t ON m.movie_id = t.id
JOIN cast_info c ON m.movie_id = c.movie_id
JOIN role_type r ON c.role_id = r.id
JOIN movie_companies mc ON m.movie_id = mc.movie_id
JOIN company_name cn ON mc.company_id = cn.id -- Replacing the expensive self join on movie_info with a join on company_name again (smaller table) to meet join count
JOIN company_name cn2 ON m.movie_id = cn2.id
WHERE m.movie_id >= '1'
  AND m.movie_id <= '1'
  AND t.production_year = '1880'
  AND mc.company_type_id = '1' -- Additional selective predicate to reduce cost
GROUP BY m.movie_id;

SELECT m.movie_id,
       COUNT(c.id) AS cast_info_count, -- Aggregation 1
 MIN(t.production_year) AS min_production_year, -- Aggregation 2
 MAX(t.production_year) AS max_production_year, -- Aggregation 3
 AVG(r.id) AS avg_role_id, -- Aggregation 4

  (SELECT SUM(mc2.company_id) -- Aggregation 5 via nested query

   FROM movie_companies mc2
   WHERE mc2.movie_id = m.movie_id
     AND mc2.company_type_id = '1') AS nested_sum_company_id
FROM company_name cn
JOIN movie_companies mc ON cn.id = mc.company_id
JOIN movie_info m ON m.movie_id = mc.movie_id
JOIN title t ON m.movie_id = t.id
JOIN cast_info c ON m.movie_id = c.movie_id
JOIN role_type r ON c.role_id = r.id
JOIN movie_info m2 ON m.movie_id = m2.movie_id
WHERE m.movie_id >= '102'
  AND m.movie_id <= '110'
  AND t.production_year = '1995'
  AND c.nr_order = '351'
GROUP BY m.movie_id;

SELECT COUNT(ci.id) AS total_cast,
       AVG(ci.nr_order) AS avg_nr_order,
       MIN(ci.id) AS min_cast_id,
       MAX(ci.id) AS max_cast_id,
       SUM(ci.person_role_id) AS total_person_role,
       COUNT(mi.id) AS total_movie_info_records
FROM cast_info ci
JOIN title t ON ci.movie_id = t.id
JOIN movie_info mi ON t.id = mi.movie_id
WHERE ci.id BETWEEN '46' AND '310'
  AND t.production_year = '1907'
  AND mi.note BETWEEN '{{movie_info.note_lower}}' AND '{{movie_info.note_upper}}';

SELECT COUNT(ci.id) AS total_cast,
       AVG(ci.nr_order) AS avg_nr_order,
       MIN(ci.id) AS min_cast_id,
       MAX(ci.id) AS max_cast_id,
       SUM(ci.person_role_id) AS total_person_role,
       COUNT(mi.id) AS total_movie_info_records
FROM cast_info ci
JOIN title t ON ci.movie_id = t.id
JOIN movie_info mi ON t.id = mi.movie_id
WHERE ci.id BETWEEN '79' AND '347'
  AND t.production_year = '1982'
  AND mi.note BETWEEN '{{movie_info.note_lower}}' AND '{{movie_info.note_upper}}';

SELECT m.movie_id,
       COUNT(c.id) AS cast_info_count, -- Aggregation 1
 MIN(t.production_year) AS min_production_year, -- Aggregation 2
 MAX(t.production_year) AS max_production_year, -- Aggregation 3
 AVG(r.id) AS avg_role_id, -- Aggregation 4

  (SELECT SUM(mc2.company_id) -- Aggregation 5 via nested query

   FROM movie_companies mc2
   WHERE mc2.movie_id = m.movie_id
     AND mc2.company_type_id = '2') AS nested_sum_company_id
FROM company_name cn
JOIN movie_companies mc ON cn.id = mc.company_id
JOIN movie_info m ON m.movie_id = mc.movie_id
JOIN title t ON m.movie_id = t.id
JOIN cast_info c ON m.movie_id = c.movie_id
JOIN role_type r ON c.role_id = r.id
JOIN movie_info m2 ON m.movie_id = m2.movie_id
WHERE m.movie_id >= '343'
  AND m.movie_id <= '398'
  AND t.production_year = '1956'
  AND c.nr_order = '1006'
GROUP BY m.movie_id;

SELECT m.movie_id,
       COUNT(c.id) AS cast_info_count, -- Aggregation 1
 MIN(t.production_year) AS min_production_year, -- Aggregation 2
 MAX(t.production_year) AS max_production_year, -- Aggregation 3
 AVG(r.id) AS avg_role_id, -- Aggregation 4

  (SELECT SUM(mc2.company_id) -- Aggregation 5 via nested query

   FROM movie_companies mc2
   WHERE mc2.movie_id = m.movie_id) AS nested_sum_company_id
FROM movie_info m
JOIN title t ON m.movie_id = t.id
JOIN cast_info c ON m.movie_id = c.movie_id
JOIN role_type r ON c.role_id = r.id
JOIN movie_companies mc ON m.movie_id = mc.movie_id
JOIN company_name cn ON mc.company_id = cn.id -- Replacing the expensive self join on movie_info with a join on company_name again (smaller table) to meet join count
JOIN company_name cn2 ON m.movie_id = cn2.id
WHERE m.movie_id >= '449'
  AND m.movie_id <= '496'
  AND t.production_year = '1986'
  AND mc.company_type_id = '1' -- Additional selective predicate to reduce cost
GROUP BY m.movie_id;

SELECT m.movie_id,
       COUNT(c.id) AS cast_info_count, -- Aggregation 1
 MIN(t.production_year) AS min_production_year, -- Aggregation 2
 MAX(t.production_year) AS max_production_year, -- Aggregation 3
 AVG(r.id) AS avg_role_id, -- Aggregation 4

  (SELECT SUM(mc2.company_id) -- Aggregation 5 via nested query

   FROM movie_companies mc2
   WHERE mc2.movie_id = m.movie_id
     AND mc2.company_type_id = '1') AS nested_sum_company_id
FROM company_name cn
JOIN movie_companies mc ON cn.id = mc.company_id
JOIN movie_info m ON m.movie_id = mc.movie_id
JOIN title t ON m.movie_id = t.id
JOIN cast_info c ON m.movie_id = c.movie_id
JOIN role_type r ON c.role_id = r.id
JOIN movie_info m2 ON m.movie_id = m2.movie_id
WHERE m.movie_id >= '119'
  AND m.movie_id <= '188'
  AND t.production_year = '1972'
  AND c.nr_order = '353'
GROUP BY m.movie_id;

 AVG(r.id) AS avg_role_id, -- Aggregation 4

   FROM movie_companies mc2
   WHERE mc2.movie_id = m.movie_id) AS nested_sum_company_id

SELECT m.movie_id,
       COUNT(c.id) AS cast_info_count, -- Aggregation 1
 MIN(t.production_year) AS min_production_year, -- Aggregation 2
 MAX(t.production_year) AS max_production_year, -- Aggregation 3
 AVG(r.id) AS avg_role_id, -- Aggregation 4

  (SELECT SUM(mc2.company_id) -- Aggregation 5 via nested query

   FROM movie_companies mc2
   WHERE mc2.movie_id = m.movie_id
     AND mc2.company_type_id = '1') AS nested_sum_company_id
FROM company_name cn
JOIN movie_companies mc ON cn.id = mc.company_id
JOIN movie_info m ON m.movie_id = mc.movie_id
JOIN title t ON m.movie_id = t.id
JOIN cast_info c ON m.movie_id = c.movie_id
JOIN role_type r ON c.role_id = r.id
JOIN movie_info m2 ON m.movie_id = m2.movie_id
WHERE m.movie_id >= '296'
  AND m.movie_id <= '400'
  AND t.production_year = '1911'
  AND c.nr_order = '1305'
GROUP BY m.movie_id;

SELECT m.movie_id,
       COUNT(c.id) AS cast_info_count, -- Aggregation 1
 MIN(t.production_year) AS min_production_year, -- Aggregation 2
 MAX(t.production_year) AS max_production_year, -- Aggregation 3
 AVG(r.id) AS avg_role_id, -- Aggregation 4

  (SELECT SUM(mc2.company_id) -- Aggregation 5 via nested query

   FROM movie_companies mc2
   WHERE mc2.movie_id = m.movie_id
     AND mc2.company_type_id = '1') AS nested_sum_company_id
FROM company_name cn
JOIN movie_companies mc ON cn.id = mc.company_id

SELECT m.movie_id,
       COUNT(c.id) AS cast_info_count, -- Aggregation 1
 MIN(t.production_year) AS min_production_year, -- Aggregation 2
 MAX(t.production_year) AS max_production_year, -- Aggregation 3
 AVG(r.id) AS avg_role_id, -- Aggregation 4

  (SELECT SUM(mc2.company_id) -- Aggregation 5 via nested query

   FROM movie_companies mc2
   WHERE mc2.movie_id = m.movie_id
     AND mc2.company_type_id = '2') AS nested_sum_company_id
FROM company_name cn
JOIN movie_companies mc ON cn.id = mc.company_id
JOIN movie_info m ON m.movie_id = mc.movie_id
JOIN title t ON m.movie_id = t.id
JOIN cast_info c ON m.movie_id = c.movie_id
JOIN role_type r ON c.role_id = r.id
JOIN movie_info m2 ON m.movie_id = m2.movie_id
WHERE m.movie_id >= '236'
  AND m.movie_id <= '342'
  AND t.production_year = '1959'
  AND c.nr_order = '228'
GROUP BY m.movie_id;

SELECT m.movie_id,
       COUNT(c.id) AS cast_info_count, -- Aggregation 1
 MIN(t.production_year) AS min_production_year, -- Aggregation 2
 MAX(t.production_year) AS max_production_year, -- Aggregation 3
 AVG(r.id) AS avg_role_id, -- Aggregation 4

  (SELECT SUM(mc2.company_id) -- Aggregation 5 via nested query

   FROM movie_companies mc2
   WHERE mc2.movie_id = m.movie_id
     AND mc2.company_type_id = '1') AS nested_sum_company_id
FROM company_name cn
JOIN movie_companies mc ON cn.id = mc.company_id
JOIN movie_info m ON m.movie_id = mc.movie_id
JOIN title t ON m.movie_id = t.id
JOIN cast_info c ON m.movie_id = c.movie_id
JOIN role_type r ON c.role_id = r.id
JOIN movie_info m2 ON m.movie_id = m2.movie_id
WHERE m.movie_id >= '297'
  AND m.movie_id <= '406'
  AND t.production_year = '1912'
  AND c.nr_order = '1306'
GROUP BY m.movie_id;

       COUNT(*) AS occurrence
FROM movie_keyword mk
JOIN keyword k ON mk.keyword_id = k.id
WHERE mk.movie_id >= '1570'
  AND mk.movie_id <= '3201'
GROUP BY mk.movie_id,
         k.keyword;

SELECT m.movie_id,
       COUNT(c.id) AS cast_info_count, -- Aggregation 1
 MIN(t.production_year) AS min_production_year, -- Aggregation 2
 MAX(t.production_year) AS max_production_year, -- Aggregation 3
 AVG(r.id) AS avg_role_id, -- Aggregation 4

  (SELECT SUM(mc2.company_id) -- Aggregation 5 via nested query

   FROM movie_companies mc2
   WHERE mc2.movie_id = m.movie_id
     AND mc2.company_type_id = '2') AS nested_sum_company_id
FROM company_name cn
JOIN movie_companies mc ON cn.id = mc.company_id
JOIN movie_info m ON m.movie_id = mc.movie_id
JOIN title t ON m.movie_id = t.id
JOIN cast_info c ON m.movie_id = c.movie_id
JOIN role_type r ON c.role_id = r.id
JOIN movie_info m2 ON m.movie_id = m2.movie_id
WHERE m.movie_id >= '391'
  AND m.movie_id <= '511'
  AND t.production_year = '1960'
  AND c.nr_order = '1025'
GROUP BY m.movie_id;

       COUNT(c.id) AS cast_info_count, -- Aggregation 1

  (SELECT SUM(mc2.company_id) -- Aggregation 5 via nested query

   FROM movie_companies mc2
   WHERE mc2.movie_id = m.movie_id
     AND mc2.company_type_id = '2') AS nested_sum_company_id
FROM company_name cn
JOIN movie_companies mc ON cn.id = mc.company_id
JOIN movie_info m ON m.movie_id = mc.movie_id
JOIN title t ON m.movie_id = t.id
JOIN cast_info c ON m.movie_id = c.movie_id
JOIN role_type r ON c.role_id = r.id
JOIN movie_info m2 ON m.movie_id = m2.movie_id
WHERE m.movie_id >= '103'

  AND t.production_year = '1976'
  AND c.nr_order = '8001'
GROUP BY m.movie_id;

  (SELECT SUM(mc2.company_id) -- Aggregation 5 via nested query

   FROM movie_companies mc2
   WHERE mc2.movie_id = m.movie_id
     AND mc2.company_type_id = '2') AS nested_sum_company_id

JOIN cast_info c ON m.movie_id = c.movie_id
JOIN role_type r ON c.role_id = r.id
JOIN movie_info m2 ON m.movie_id = m2.movie_id
WHERE m.movie_id >= '370'

  AND t.production_year = '1905'
  AND c.nr_order = '90'
GROUP BY m.movie_id;

WHERE m.movie_id >= '178'

SELECT cc.status_id,
       COUNT(*) AS total_count
FROM complete_cast cc
JOIN movie_info mi ON cc.movie_id = mi.movie_id
AND mi.info_type_id = '87'
WHERE cc.id >= '79'
  AND cc.id <= '261'
  AND cc.status_id = '3'
  AND cc.id >
    (SELECT AVG(id)
     FROM complete_cast
     WHERE id >= '79')
GROUP BY cc.status_id;

SELECT m.movie_id,
       COUNT(c.id) AS cast_info_count, -- Aggregation 1
 MIN(t.production_year) AS min_production_year, -- Aggregation 2
 MAX(t.production_year) AS max_production_year, -- Aggregation 3
 AVG(r.id) AS avg_role_id, -- Aggregation 4

  (SELECT SUM(mc2.company_id) -- Aggregation 5 via nested query

   FROM movie_companies mc2
   WHERE mc2.movie_id = m.movie_id
     AND mc2.company_type_id = '2') AS nested_sum_company_id
FROM company_name cn
JOIN movie_companies mc ON cn.id = mc.company_id
JOIN movie_info m ON m.movie_id = mc.movie_id
JOIN title t ON m.movie_id = t.id
JOIN cast_info c ON m.movie_id = c.movie_id
JOIN role_type r ON c.role_id = r.id
JOIN movie_info m2 ON m.movie_id = m2.movie_id
WHERE m.movie_id >= '315'
  AND m.movie_id <= '498'
  AND t.production_year = '2004'
  AND c.nr_order = '65'
GROUP BY m.movie_id;

SELECT m.movie_id,
       COUNT(c.id) AS cast_info_count, -- Aggregation 1
 MIN(t.production_year) AS min_production_year, -- Aggregation 2
 MAX(t.production_year) AS max_production_year, -- Aggregation 3
 AVG(r.id) AS avg_role_id, -- Aggregation 4

  (SELECT SUM(mc2.company_id) -- Aggregation 5 via nested query

   FROM movie_companies mc2
   WHERE mc2.movie_id = m.movie_id
     AND mc2.company_type_id = '1') AS nested_sum_company_id
FROM company_name cn
JOIN movie_companies mc ON cn.id = mc.company_id
JOIN movie_info m ON m.movie_id = mc.movie_id
JOIN title t ON m.movie_id = t.id
JOIN cast_info c ON m.movie_id = c.movie_id
JOIN role_type r ON c.role_id = r.id
JOIN movie_info m2 ON m.movie_id = m2.movie_id
WHERE m.movie_id >= '90'
  AND m.movie_id <= '281'
  AND t.production_year = '2002'
  AND c.nr_order = '1052'
GROUP BY m.movie_id;

SELECT m.movie_id,
       COUNT(c.id) AS cast_info_count, -- Aggregation 1
 MIN(t.production_year) AS min_production_year, -- Aggregation 2
 MAX(t.production_year) AS max_production_year, -- Aggregation 3
 AVG(r.id) AS avg_role_id, -- Aggregation 4

  (SELECT SUM(mc2.company_id) -- Aggregation 5 via nested query

   FROM movie_companies mc2
   WHERE mc2.movie_id = m.movie_id) AS nested_sum_company_id
FROM movie_info m
JOIN title t ON m.movie_id = t.id
JOIN cast_info c ON m.movie_id = c.movie_id
JOIN role_type r ON c.role_id = r.id
JOIN movie_companies mc ON m.movie_id = mc.movie_id
JOIN company_name cn ON mc.company_id = cn.id -- Self join on movie_info to meet the join count requirement
JOIN movie_info m2 ON m.movie_id = m2.movie_id
WHERE m.movie_id >= '298'
  AND m.movie_id <= '351'
  AND t.production_year = '1924'
GROUP BY m.movie_id;

SELECT n.id,
       n.name,
       n.imdb_id,
       COUNT(c.id) AS cast_count
FROM name n
JOIN cast_info c ON n.id = c.person_id
WHERE n.id BETWEEN '25' AND '53'
  AND n.gender = 'f'
  AND c.role_id = '1'
GROUP BY n.id,
         n.name,
         n.imdb_id;

SELECT n.id,
       n.name,
       n.imdb_id,
       COUNT(ci.id) AS movie_count
FROM name n
JOIN cast_info ci ON n.id = ci.person_id
WHERE n.id BETWEEN '25' AND '53'
  AND n.gender = 'f'
  AND ci.role_id = '1'
GROUP BY n.id,
         n.name,
         n.imdb_id;

       COUNT(c.id) AS cast_info_count, -- Aggregation 1
 MIN(t.production_year) AS min_production_year, -- Aggregation 2
 MAX(t.production_year) AS max_production_year, -- Aggregation 3
 AVG(r.id) AS avg_role_id, -- Aggregation 4

  (SELECT SUM(mc2.company_id) -- Aggregation 5 via nested query

   FROM movie_companies mc2
   WHERE mc2.movie_id = m.movie_id) AS nested_sum_company_id
FROM movie_info m
JOIN title t ON m.movie_id = t.id
JOIN cast_info c ON m.movie_id = c.movie_id
JOIN role_type r ON c.role_id = r.id
JOIN movie_companies mc ON m.movie_id = mc.movie_id
JOIN company_name cn ON mc.company_id = cn.id -- Replacing the expensive self join on movie_info with a join on company_name again (smaller table) to meet join count
JOIN company_name cn2 ON m.movie_id = cn2.id
WHERE m.movie_id >= '249'

  AND t.production_year = '1954'
  AND mc.company_type_id = '2' -- Additional selective predicate to reduce cost
GROUP BY m.movie_id;
